the associated press reported erroneously march 18 that a book written by former white house chief of staff donald t. regan would be published nine months later than originally planned
the book, being published by harcourt brace jovanovich, will be issued this may, four months earlier than first planned, not nine months later, the publishing house reported
police academy 5: assignment miami beach,'' grabbed first place in weekend box office receipts, dislodging ``good morning, vietnam'' after nine weeks at the top and preventing it from setting a record
police academy 5'' from warner bros. earned $6.1 million in its debut weekend, while disney-touchstone's ``good morning, vietnam,'' earned more than $4 million, falling to second. the robin williams comedy's nine-straight weekends as the most nation's popular movie equaled the longest consecutive hold on no. 1 set in 1986 by the comedy ``crocodile dundee.''
the latest ``police academy'' sequel features the whole wacky crew in miami for a police convention
another debut movie, ``d.o.a.'' was third with $3.7 million in ticket sales. the disney-touchstone film stars dennis quaid and meg ryan in a remake of the 1949 thriller of the same name. quaid plays a poisoned college professor who has 24 hours to find his killer before he dies
disney-touchstone has four of the 10-top, while mgm-ua and warner bros. each have two
