cher's ``moonstruck'' earned $2.3 million for sixth place. its writer, john patrick shanley, won the writers guild of america's honor for best original screenplay last week. the movie has been nominated for six academy awards
three men and a baby'' was in seventh place with $2.1 million, and reached a $150.6 million cumulative gross
off limits,'' a story about two military undercover officers trying to solve a series of prostitute murders in saigon during the vietnam war, earned $1.58 million for eighth place
in ninth was roman polanski's ``frantic'' with $1.50 million, followed by ``shoot to kill,'' with $1.4 million
