balancing 360 eggs on their ends may not be a scientifically approved way of demonstrating the supposed powers of the first day of spring. but don't tell that to performance artist donna henes
about 200 people helped henes balance the eggs at 4:39 a.m. sunday, the precise moment of the vernal equinox, one of two points in the year when the sun crosses the equator and day and night are equal
considering the hour, more people showed up than i expected,'' she said. the egg balancing took place on a long table-like platform at the south street seaport shopping area
according to henes, balancing an egg on its end is an ancient chinese custom that brings good luck
scientists are dubious whether eggs really do balance during the equinox due to changes in the gravitational pull, but henes is convinced
it's funny, because i've asked a lot of scientists about it and they say its impossible,'' henes said. ``however, when i ask them to join in the ritual and they see it happen, they become instant believers.''
henes, who has been observing the egg-balancing ritual for the past 13 years, said eggs are ancient symbols of fertility and spring around the world. ``easter is only one of many spring holidays where the egg is used as a symbol of rebirth,'' she said
after balancing the eggs, the participants enjoyed them at a breakfast prepared by one of the tourist attraction's restaurants
