the southwest had temperatures in the 50s and 60s early today, following readings in the 80s and 90s on sunday in california and southern arizona. yuma, ariz., had the nation's high sunday with 95 degrees
the heaviest snow today was in the lower great lakes region due to squalls near shore. forecasters posted lake snow advisories in new york state along the shore of lake ontario, where up to 5 inches was possible
in the pacific northwest, heavier rainfall totals for the six-hour period ending at 1 a.m. est included about a quarter of an inch at hoquiam and fort lewis, wash
