guerrillas attacked six positions manned by an israeli-backed militia before dawn today in one of their biggest assaults this year, security sources reported
there was no immediate report of casualties and it could not be determined which guerrilla faction launched the assault on the south lebanon army outposts, the second reported clash in three days
after today's attack, israeli and south lebanon army gunners shelled the shiite moslem market town of nabatiyeh with mortars and tank cannon in an apparent retaliation for the pre-dawn raid, police said
the sources, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the guerrillas fired machine guns and rocket-propelled grenades into the south lebanon army positions in the central sector of israel's self-proclaimed ``security zone'' on the lebanon-israel border
the mainly christian south lebanon army retaliated with heavy machine guns and mortars, the sources reported
israeli troops rushed to reinforce the army positions and opened up on the raiders with tank fire, the sources said. the fighting lasted for two hours until the attackers withdrew, the sources said
several positions manned by irish and finnish troops of the united nations peacekeeping force were caught in the crossfire, but no u.n. soldiers were hurt, the sources added
the zone policed by the u.n. interim force in lebanon overlaps the israeli-occupied buffer zone carved out in june 1985 when israel withdrew the bulk of its army three years after its invaded lebanon
in the attack by israeli and south lebanon army on the moslem town, two women were wounded when five shells exploded in the sarai quarter, crowded with villagers in town for the weekly market day, police said
the 30-minute barrage brought the town of 150,000 inhabitants to a standstill. shopkeepers lowered their shutters, businesses closed and schools sent pupils home
today's hostilities came two days after tank-led israeli troops and south lebanon army militiamen raided suspected guerrilla bases four miles northeast of the security zone
shiite moslem guerrillas earlier fought a seven-hour shelling duel with the israelis and their militia allies in which two elderly lebanese civilians were wounded
israeli fighter-bombers raided a palestinian guerrilla camp in the chouf mountains southeast of beirut last thursday, killing one guerrilla in their deepest penetration into lebanon this year. cycle:</head>
