she has appeared on such shows as ``simon &amp; simon,'' ``227'' and ``it's garry shandling's show.'' engines</head>
letting a truck's diesel engine run at idle causes twice as much damage as driving, and truckers who let their rigs idle during rest stops are wasting money and diesel fuel, a researcher said monday
some truckers have a misconception that idling is good for their rigs, but researchers at argonne national laboratory found that excess idling can shorten the life of a diesel truck engine by six months to a year
there's a lot of misinformation out there (among truckers),'' said larry r. johnson, director of argonne's center for transportation research. ``they realize it's using fuel, but some of them perceive that it's good for the engine to keep it running.''
in one of a series of studies for the u.s. department of energy aimed at improving fuel efficiency in the trucking industry, johnson said argonne researchers found that one hour of idling causes as much engine wear as two hours of driving
based on interviews with trucking company officials and drivers, they calculated that a typical 18-wheeler idles about 800 hours a year, the equivalent of 64,000 miles of driving, johnson said monday in a telephone interview
he said that much idling would make the engine need an overhaul up to a year sooner than under normal driving conditions
it wears out an engine twice as fast as being under load,'' johnson said
diesel engines usually require an overhaul every five years or 500,000 miles, he said
many truckers leave their rigs running when they stop to rest as a way of keeping the engine and diesel fuel warm in the winter, and keeping the cab heated or cooled in summer, he said
but the argonne researchers found that idling in the winter cools the engine faster than if it were shut off because fans blow cold air over the engine block and fuel lines, johnson said
the lower idling temperature damages the engine by causing water vapor to condense in the crankcase, said raj sekar, a mechanical engineer at the argonne transportation center
the water mixes with unburned sulfur oxides from diesel fuel combustion and produces sulfuric acid, which corrodes the piston rings and cylinder liners, he said
the argonne researchers also calculated that the typical trucker idles his engine at least three hours each workday, wasting an estimated 800 gallons of fuel a year, johnson said
as an alternative to idling, johnson said, the argonne study recommended that truckers or trucking companies buy heaters for the fuel system, engine block, cab and sleeping compartment. he said the cost of buying each heater would pay for itself in one year through fuel savings alone
argonne, located 25 miles west of chicago, is operated by the university of chicago for the department of energy
president reagan has nominated air force lt. gen. merrill a. mcpeak for promotion to general and assignment as commander-in-chief of the pacific air forces, the pentagon said monday
assuming he is confirmed by the senate, mcpeak, 52, would receive his fourth star and the rank of full general and replace gen. jack i. gregory, 56, who will retire on aug. 1 after 35 years of active-duty service
gregory, a native of somerset, ky., has commanded the pacific air forces since december 1986. mcpeak, of santa rosa, calif., now commands the 12th air force
