jackson has also been rumored to be interested in a $5 million hotel near the ranch, but the owner of the grand hotel, william healey, said monday he has not talked with the singer or his agent
it's a rumour,'' real estate broker healey said. ``there's absolutely no truth to it.''
the ranch in the scenic santa ynez valley 100 miles northwest of los angeles was on the market for $32 million and includes a main house on a 32-acre section, a large clubhouse and 50,000 oak trees. jackson had originally offered $17 million, the los angeles times reported sunday, quoting unidentified real estate sources
his menagerie includes monkeys, llamas, snakes, birds, and barnyard animals, except for a cow
