the dow jones average of 30 industrials, which hit the highest level since the oct. 19 collapse twice last week and flirted with the 2,100-point barrier, fell 23.38 points to 2,063.99 by noon on wall street
there are very nervous people out there,'' said hank striefler, vice president on the trading floor at shearson lehman hutton inc. ``everybody is concerned. by reaching 2,100, that's sort of a top for the dow at the moment.''
among broader market indicators, the new york stock exchange composite index of all listed issues fell 1.34 to 151.31. on the american stock exchange, the market value index fell 1.39 to 297.72
